# Scenario: PSM TOO AGGRESSIVE — Quectel BG95 with Power Saving Mode enabled.
# Customer reports: "device attaches, sometimes sends one packet, then we lose it
# for 30+ minutes at a time. Then it comes back briefly and the cycle repeats."
# Key signals:
#   +CPSMS: 1,,,"00000010","00000001"   (PSM enabled, T3412=60s, T3324=10s)
#     - T3324 (active timer) = 10 seconds — modem goes to deep sleep 10s after
#       its last activity
#     - T3412 (periodic TAU) = 60 seconds — modem briefly wakes for tracking-area
#       update on this interval
#   +CEDRXS: 1,4,"0010"                 (eDRX enabled, ~20.48s paging window)
#   +CEREG: 0,1, +CGATT: 1, +CGACT OK   (all looks correct when awake)
#   +CSCON: 0,0                         (RRC IDLE — not in connected state)
# Diagnosis: PSM is doing exactly what it's configured to do. Device is asleep
# 90%+ of the time. From the platform perspective the device looks "gone" because
# downlink packets buffer at the network and only deliver during the brief
# eDRX paging windows.
# Customer guidance:
#   - For DEBUG: temporarily disable PSM/eDRX:
#       AT+CPSMS=0
#       AT+CEDRXS=0
#     Re-test data path. If problem disappears, you've confirmed PSM is the cause.
#   - For PRODUCTION: tune T3324 (active timer) longer than the device's
#     application duty cycle. If your firmware sends data every 5 minutes, T3324
#     of 10 seconds is wrong. If you need downlink within X seconds of an event,
#     PSM is incompatible — use eDRX alone or stay always-on.
# Triage flag: ALWAYS check +CPSMS? and +CEDRXS? before debugging "device
# disappears periodically" complaints. PSM-induced "outages" account for a
# surprising fraction of L2 escalations.

AT+CPIN?
+CPIN: READY
OK
AT+CPSMS?
+CPSMS: 1,,,"00000010","00000001"
OK
AT+CEDRXS?
+CEDRXS: 1,4,"0010"
OK
AT+CEREG?
+CEREG: 0,1
OK
AT+CGATT?
+CGATT: 1
OK
AT+CSCON?
+CSCON: 0,0
OK
AT+CGACT=1,1
OK
AT+CGPADDR=1
+CGPADDR: 1,"100.66.4.18"
OK
AT+CSCON?
+CSCON: 0,0
OK
